l}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". Therefore, the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":199,\"end\":216}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Tathāgata\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":216,\"end\":225},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"e73562d6-15c5-4706-82c3-8f843ccfec58\",\"uuid\":\"372a59ac-644b-4ab1-bbf8-892ff701413e\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":225,\"end\":226}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Śākyamuni\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":226,\"end\":235},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"30470857-9228-4b50-ad00-ff8c913dc02a\",\"uuid\":\"9bdf6151-d599-41f8-9d54-acfb10f43f57\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" has manifested a short lifespan in order to benefit beings with inferior aspiration, beings with little roots of merit and faith, and ordinary foolish beings who have the view that there is a being, the view that there is a soul, the view that there is a spirit, the view that there is an individual, erroneous views, the belief in ‘me’ and ‘mine,’ the views of eternalism and nihilism, and so on. It is also to inspire the true view in \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":235,\"end\":673}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"tīrthikas\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":673,\"end\":682},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"4b2c2119-6dd4-4607-afda-9c0ea3cd6860\",\"uuid\":\"122d11e6-43b7-4f79-a9b3-6317ae83c281\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" so that they will quickly attain the highest enlightenment.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":682,\"end\":742}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"aaba1478-6219-4ef5-a011-f06d44c49f7a\",\"sort\":1974,\"type\":\"translation\",\"label\":\"2.20\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":798,\"uuid\":\"aaba1478-6219-4ef5-a011-f06d44c49f7a\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"“Moreover, noble one, the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":26}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Tathāgata\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":26,\"end\":35},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"e73562d6-15c5-4706-82c3-8f843ccfec58\",\"uuid\":\"51a4bc6c-cfdd-4e69-b956-9ab8f824240d\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", by manifesting passing into \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":35,\"end\":65}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"nirvāṇa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":65,\"end\":72},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"bebe04fd-2b22-4637-89db-ae1cd69dffe1\",\"uuid\":\"505b398c-c804-45de-88df-033ee9711bd7\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", causes beings to perceive him as rare and difficult to meet; causes them to perceive misery, suffering, and so on; and inspires them to quickly obtain, possess, read, comprehend, and teach widely to others these sūtras that have been taught by the Buddha \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":72,\"end\":329}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Bhagavat\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":329,\"end\":337},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"7317e301-9d9a-41ce-9424-338eceefcc6b\",\"uuid\":\"4af45f9c-15ef-4fc9-a396-61eaa1ffdead\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", and to not malign them. That is why the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":337,\"end\":379}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Tathāgata\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":379,\"end\":388},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"e73562d6-15c5-4706-82c3-8f843ccfec58\",\"uuid\":\"8e44d70d-a9bd-4cdd-af70-87fa55d7d8ec\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" manifests a short lifespan. If the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":388,\"end\":424}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Tathāgata\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":424,\"end\":433},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"e73562d6-15c5-4706-82c3-8f843ccfec58\",\"uuid\":\"498fc975-6079-4cbf-b3af-ee976d02909a\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" were always present and did not pass into \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":433,\"end\":476}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"nirvāṇa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":476,\"end\":483},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"bebe04fd-2b22-4637-89db-ae1cd69dffe1\",\"uuid\":\"09528735-c7d6-4b3c-9a62-ec9a116ea4c8\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", beings would have no reverence‍—they would not perceive him as being difficult to meet, and they would not obtain, possess, read, comprehend, and teach widely to others these sūtras that have been taught by the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":483,\"end\":696}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Tathāgata\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":696,\"end\":705},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"e73562d6-15c5-4706-82c3-8f843ccfec58\",\"uuid\":\"e57a789d-9c9e-4f12-9308-215a3973039f\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". Why is that? Because they would believe that the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":705,\"end\":756}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Bhagavat\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":756,\"end\":764},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"7317e301-9d9a-41ce-9424-338eceefcc6b\",\"uuid\":\"b968ba05-ff8a-4680-bd1d-f8ba8e375d7c\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" would always remain in the world.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":764,\"end\":798}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"378ebeb6-3336-4ee3-9d38-568fb44e2f7f\",\"sort\":1994,\"type\":\"translation\",\"label\":\"2.21\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":351,\"uuid\":\"378ebeb6-3336-4ee3-9d38-568fb44e2f7f\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"“As an analogy, noble one, someone who sees that his parents have many precious jewels would not perceive that wealth as being rare or wonderful. Why is that? It is because he perceives that his parents’ wealth will always be present. In the same way, if the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":259}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Bhagavat\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":259,\"end\":267},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"7317e301-9d9a-41ce-9424-338eceefcc6b\",\"uuid\":\"ef0ae2e3-e90c-4d90-b24e-2b7b296793f5\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" never passed into \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":267,\"end\":286}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"nirvāṇa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":286,\"end\":293},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"bebe04fd-2b22-4637-89db-ae1cd69dffe1\",\"uuid\":\"353233ad-1611-42ec-97af-e68a56db2dad\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", he would not be perceived as rare and difficult to meet.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":293,\"end\":351}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"3c5386ca-88e2-4733-b9ae-310e9702d6f2\",\"sort\":2000,\"type\":\"translation\",\"label\":\"2.22\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":434,\"uuid\":\"3c5386ca-88e2-4733-b9ae-310e9702d6f2\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"“Moreover, noble one, as another analogy, if someone who had poor parents, who had no wealth, went to the dwelling of a king or great minister and saw their vast, numerous treasuries, wealth, jewels and so on, he would perceive them as rare and difficult to obtain, and he would dedicate himself to accomplishing the methods for seeking wealth, because he would wish to leave poverty behind and to accomplish happiness and prosperity.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":434}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"f401b3e7-49de-40f4-9783-2dd70cd1e006\",\"sort\":2002,\"type\":\"translation\",\"label\":\"2.23\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":543,\"uuid\":\"f401b3e7-49de-40f4-9783-2dd70cd1e006\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"“In the same way, noble one, if the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":36}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Tathāgata\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":36,\"end\":45},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"e73562d6-15c5-4706-82c